<http://www.spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/event/51001ARVGTVPPNTBQGVCQJBVQPDQSJLSM>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Blues Odyssey 2026";
  schema:description """
	Get ready for <span class=\"BoldText\">The Odyssey</span>, the soul-stirring grand finale of the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.hornbyblues.ca/\">Hornby Island Blues Society</a>'s annual Blues Week. After a week of intensive workshops and concerts, Canada's blues elite are crossing the water for one legendary night at the Tidemark Theatre.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Witness a spectacular musical collaboration as these award-winning artists move from mentors to masters on the big stage. This is more than just a concert; it’s a \"Blues Review\" featuring a \"who's who\" of contemporary Canadian talent, collectively boasting Junos, Maple Blues Awards, and International Blues Challenge honors.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Featuring:<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><ul><li> Angel Forrest</li><li> Ndidi Onukwulu</li><li> Paul Pigat</li><li> Brandon Isaak</li><li> Steve Strongman</li><li> Steve Marriner</li><li> Terry Robb</li><li> Steve Dawson</li><li> Ethan Askey</li><li> Jesse O'Brien</li><li> Suzie Vinnick</li><li> Damian Graham</li><li> Rob Lutes</li></ul><span><br/></span>Tickets: $65.00 Admission <span class=\"ItalicText\">(+applicable taxes & fees)</span>
""";
