<http://www.spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/event/43201AJDRNMMDNNQTNJHJVCVNCQGVJMVN>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "CRFF Local's Showcase";
  schema:description """
	Come enjoy the creative works of local filmmakers! This night will feature a series of short films from a variety of genres that are filmed by filmmakers from the northern Vancouver Island region.  You'll be surprised to discover the professional skills and local stories featured in these films.  There will be opportunities to chat with the various filmmakers in attendance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Congratulations to the independent filmmakers accepted into this year's Showcase:<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Raining Glory: Campbell River by Night </span></span>(3.5 min)<span><br/></span>Filmaker: Neall Calvert<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“Raining Glory” is a 3.5-minute video featuring 40 images of Campbell River taken after midnight, during rainstorms, through the front windshield of a vehicle. It is set to a music score titled “The Light Between Us.”<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Christie Residential School Gathering </span></span>(10.48 min)<span><br/></span>Filmaker: Gord Kurbis<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Survivors of the former Christie Residential School returned to Meares Island in October of 2025 to attend a ‘Healing Gathering’. The event was held so they could witness the emotional demolition of the final buildings used by the troubled educational institution.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">This Is Where I live </span></span>(4+ min)<span><br/></span>Filmaker: Daniel Hillert<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Summer mornings often begin beneath a soft veil of fog that drifts in from the ocean…<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">We Were Here </span></span>(25.16 min)<span><br/></span>Filmaker: Damian Stevenson<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tap into the elder knowledge of North Island queer seniors on a rainbow-woven journey through their life stories and their hopes for the uncertain future ahead.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets: $20.00 Admission <span class=\"ItalicText\">(+applicable taxes & fees)</span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-03-03T19:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/files/03b06474-75fd-4597-9bd7-02059ef0cb54.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/location/405AGDKDKNLGVLJCSNTLQBVTRTGBTHCPJ>;
  schema:url <https://tidemarktheatre.com/event/crff-locals-showcase/>;
  schema:offers _:d25bd24b203747b0805b2b5a2fe2a7927153;
  schema:duration "PT120M";
  schema:endDate "2026-03-03T21:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

