<http://www.spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/event/45201ARKHJCBNTTPVRDPLBGRLGJLSLDSJ>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Rotary Honours Concert";
  schema:description """
	Rotarians have long been committed to serving youth in their communities. The <span class=\"ItalicText\">New</span> <span class=\"ItalicText\">Generations Avenue of Service</span> – which became Rotary’s fifth “Avenue of Service” in 2010 – streamlines the exceptional work that Rotarians do with youth and young adults.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Rotary’s annual “Gift to the City,” The <span class=\"ItalicText\">Rotary Honours Concert,</span> exemplifies this commitment and celebrates the artistic talents of exceptional young people in our community. It speaks to the incredible dedication of the teachers and parents in keeping the artistic threads of the past alive to pass on to future generations. The award winners chosen to perform in tonight's concert showcase this artistic talent, as well as the exceptional variety and scope of the arts available in our community.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets are free of charge!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>First come, first served. Limit 4 tickets per household. Please indicate at the time of reservation if you require wheelchair seating.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Every body that goes into the auditorium MUST have a ticket, including infants.
""";
